Chunk 1 complete. Files created:

- **`src/server/services/sse-broadcaster.ts`** — Redis pub/sub SSE broadcaster with `publishSSE(orgId, type, data)` and `subscribeSSE(orgId)`. Separate Redis connections for pub vs sub (ioredis requirement). Heartbeat every 30s. Supports 5 event types: `workflow_status`, `post_status`, `budget_warning`, `outlier_detected`, `account_health`.

- **`src/app/api/sse/[orgId]/route.ts`** — Next.js route handler streaming SSE. Auth-gated (checks session exists + `session.organizationId === orgId`). Cleans up subscriber on client disconnect via `AbortSignal`.

- **No middleware change needed** — `/api/sse` is not in `PUBLIC_ROUTES`, so it already requires auth through the existing middleware flow. The route handler does its own session + orgId verification.

Couldn't run `tsc --noEmit` — deps not installable in worktree (`next-auth@^5.0.0` resolution issue). Code follows existing patterns exactly (Redis from ioredis, auth from `@/server/auth/config`).

